<!--
  Aizuchi iOS Info.plist additions required by tauri-plugin-aizuchi-audio.

  The Tauri iOS bundler emits the per-app Info.plist into
  `src-tauri/gen/apple/<app>.xcodeproj/<app>_iOS/Info.plist` on first
  `tauri ios init`. The `src-tauri/Info.plist` in this repo is the
  shared template Tauri reads first; the keys below need to be present
  in whichever Plist actually ships in the iOS bundle.

  Drop the two keys below into the existing <dict> at the top level.
  Do NOT replace the existing `NSMicrophoneUsageDescription` — it's
  already correct for the desktop path and the same string works on
  iOS.
-->
<key>NSMicrophoneUsageDescription</key>
<string>Aizuchi captures your meeting audio to transcribe it into a live mind-map. Audio stays on your device — nothing is sent to a server.</string>

<key>UIBackgroundModes</key>
<array>
    <!--
      Required so AVAudioEngine keeps delivering tap callbacks when
      the screen is locked or the user switches apps mid-meeting.
      Without this, iOS suspends the audio engine within ~30 seconds
      of the app going to the background.

      App Review flags background-audio entitlements aggressively;
      see app-review-notes.md for the reviewer framing.
    -->
    <string>audio</string>
</array>
